ZH: 他试图掩饰自己的紧张情绪。
EN: He tried to conceal his nervousness.

ZH: 她戴着墨镜，想要掩饰自己的眼袋。
EN: She wore sunglasses to hide her under-eye bags.

ZH: 对方不断掩饰他们的真实意图。
EN: The other party constantly concealed their true intentions.

ZH: 他的微笑只是用来掩饰内心的不安。
EN: His smile was only a cover for his inner unease.

ZH: 她穿着显瘦的衣服，试图掩饰自己的赘肉。
EN: She wore slimming clothes to hide her excess fat.

ZH: 不要掩饰你的错误，应该勇敢面对。
EN: Don't cover up your mistakes, you should face them bravely.

ZH: 他对事实进行了掩饰，而不是坦白承认。
EN: He concealed the truth instead of admitting it honestly.

ZH: 她总是用幽默来掩饰自己的不自信。
EN: She always uses humor to camouflage her lack of confidence.

ZH: 公司高层试图掩饰公司的财务问题。
EN: The top management of the company tried to conceal the financial issues.

ZH: 他想尽一切办法掩饰他的真实身份。
EN: He tried every possible means to hide his true identity.

ZH: 这个政府一直在掩饰真相。
EN: This government has been concealing the truth.

ZH: 她的冷笑只是为了掩饰自己的失望。
EN: Her cynical laughter was just a cover for her disappointment.

ZH: 他的自信只是用来掩饰内心的自卑感。
EN: His self-assuredness was just a camouflage for his inner insecurity.

ZH: 我试图掩饰我的紧张情绪，但是还是被别人察觉到了。
EN: I tried to conceal my nervousness, but someone still noticed.

ZH: 她总是用嘲笑来掩饰自己的羡慕之情。
EN: She always uses mockery to mask her envy.

ZH: 她用大声笑来掩饰自己的害羞。
EN: She uses loud laughter to hide her shyness.

ZH: 我不想掩饰我的痛苦，我要发泄出来。
EN: I don't want to conceal my pain, I want to let it out.

ZH: 他的演技很高超，能够很好地掩饰自己的情绪。
EN: His acting skills are excellent, he can conceal his emotions very well.

ZH: 她试图掩饰自己的流泪，但眼泪还是滑落了下来。
EN: She tried to hide her tears, but they still fell.

ZH: 外婆用冷淡来掩饰她的内心痛苦。
EN: Grandma uses indifference to conceal her inner pain.

ZH: 我们不能再掩饰真相了，该面对现实。
EN: We can't conceal the truth anymore, we have to face reality.
